∀ k, k ∈ derivations → k ∈ derivations ∧ derivations.meth k = derivations.meth n
∀ x ∈ G.Z, ∀ n, (n ∈ u → ∃ m ∈ v, (n, m) ∈ derivations ∧ m = x ∧ derivations.meth x = derivations.meth n) →
∀ k, k ∈ derivations → k ∈ derivations ∧ derivations.meth k = derivations.meth n
This condition is complex and its precise definition is not needed for the proof.
It is sufficient to know that it implies injectivity of the derivation map and
that the derivation tree is complete. The exhaustive condition is assumed to hold
for the initial derivation `cfd`.
